The paper discusses the requirements engineering of adaptive systems, which involves the use of quantitative and qualitative variables, as well as monitoring and control of requirements. This suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions control loops, which are commonly used in systems and control engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the relaxation of requirements, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL) and the evaluation of partial satisfaction, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
